.TH "MANUAL" "1" "26 JULY 2023" "0.1" "Simple Shell man page"

.SH NAME
Simple Shell \- Command line interpreter for Linux OS

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The Simple Shell is a command-line interpreter for Linux operating systems. The shell is the user interface that allows users to interact with the operating system by entering and executing commands. It interprets and executes the commands a user enters, serving as the interface between the user and the system. The shell is often referred to as a command interpreter.

.SH Overview
The Simple Shell reads lines from either a file or the terminal, interprets them, and implements various commands. When a user logs into the system, the shell is the program that is started. It provides features to facilitate interactive use and supports both interactive and non-interactive use through shell scripts. Commands can be typed directly into the running shell or put into a file that can be executed by the shell.

.SH Return Value
The Simple Shell returns 0 for success and a non-zero value for failure.

.SH PATH
The Simple Shell will look for executable commands in all the directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

.SH OPTIONS
The Simple Shell command options are typed after the main command, followed by a space and a '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLES
Running a command with options:
.B
$ ls -l

.SH BUGS
A single space is required after each argument.

